3. Nc3
{ I am recommending this dynamic move. White threatens to play 4.e4 and dominate the center. This concrete approach has been employed numerous times recently by many top GMs, most notably Aronian. He scored important victories against strong opposition such as Vachier, Nepomniachtchi, Rapport, Jones, etc. }
3... c5
{ This move is not good for Black, as it leads to an inferior version of the Benoni Defence. }
4. d5
{ White needs to fight for space advantage immediately. With the pawn on c2 now instead of on c4 in many Benoni variations, White has more flexible options here. As a general rule, White should meet ...a6 with a4, and play for the central break with e2-e4-e5. The f3-knight can also be relocated to c4 via d2. }
4... Bg7 5. e4 d6
