4... exd5
{ This move releases the tension in the center but allows the white queen to centralize. }
5. Nxd5 Nxd5 6. Qxd5
{ The white queen is very active on d5 and cannot be chased away easily. } 6...
Nc6 { Black wants to play ... d6 and ... Be6 quickly. } 7. Bg5
{ White develops the bishop with tempo by attacking the black queen. Black faces a difficult decision now: if he exchanges the bishops with ... Be7, the c5-pawn will be vulnerable. Otherwise, it is not clear how Black can finish his development. }
7... Qb6 8. Ne5
{ If White does not play this move, Black would be fine with ... d6 followed by ...Be6. }
