10... O-O 11. g3 Ng7 12. Bg2 Nf5 13. Bf4
{ White is better positionally, mainly due to Black's passive bishop on c8. We will exchange the dark-squared bishops, then play O-O, Nf3, Re1 with good control over the center. In the long-term, we can start a kingside attack with h2-h4-h5, Qd2, Ng5, etc. }
