7. Ne5 { This move stops ...Nh5 and creates pressure on Black's kingside. }
7... O-O 8. Bd3 Nd7 { Black must try to neutralize the pressure. } 9. O-O Ndxe5
10. dxe5 f5
{ This move gets rid of the white pawn on e5 but slightly weakens Black’s kingside. }
11. exf6 Bxf6 12. Bg3
{ White has more active pieces, and the black kingside is slightly vulnerable. White will play Re1, e4 and start the attack in the center. }
