{ 14... h6 is a mistake because after 15. O-O-O Qxd4 16. Rxd4, Black is left with a passive position and the big weakness on b7. }
15. Bf3 Qxd4 16. cxd4
{ Even with an isolated pawn on d4, White is better thanks to our active bishop. White will continue with Ke2, Rac1, Rhd1 and attack the black pawns. }
