{ Recapture with the e-pawn when the black knight is on c6 has two benefits. First of all, Black does not have Nb4. Secondly, we open up the e-file for our rook while Black's pieces are not well placed. Ideally, Black wants to have the knight on d7 instead of c6 in order to keep the long diagonal open for his bishop. }
10... d6 11. Re1 Re8 12. Ne4
{ All of White's pieces are centralized and active. We will play a4, Qe2 next and start attacking in the center or on the queenside. }
