4. e3 Bb7
{ This move is a logical follow-up of the previous move. However, I also analyzed a few other options for Black. }
5. Bd3
{ I am recommending this move for White. We delay the move Nbd2 because this knight may be better placed on c3 in some cases, as you will see later. We should prioritize developing our kingside and aiming for e3-e4. }
5... Be7
{ Black develops his bishop naturally and creates the positional threat of ...Nh5 at the same time. }
6. h3
{ This standard move neutralizes the Nh5 threat by allowing our bishop a retreat to h2 when necessary. }
6... c5 7. c3
