15. e4
{ White should challenge Black's center now. The threat is simply exd5. } 15...
O-O 16. a5
{ Whenever it is possible, White should advance the queenside pawns. Black cannot take on a5 twice.  16...Rxa5  17.Rxa5  Qxa5  18.e5  wins a piece for White. }
16... c4 17. b6 Qb8 18. h3
{ We have a very untraditional position with chances for both sides. I feel it is harder to play for Black as his king is slightly more exposed. White wants to capture on g4 and then castle short. In some cases, White may also bring the queenside rook to attack the black king along the third rank. }
