Bg5 c6
{ The tactics, starting with the following sharp move, all work in White's favor now. }
8. e4 dxe4 9. Ne5
{ The f7-pawn becomes a fatal weakness for Black. If  9...Qe7  10.Bc4  Be6  11.d5  Bxd5  12.Nxd5  Qxe5  then  13.Bf4  wins the black queen. }
9... Be6 10. Bc4
{ As Black is behind in development, it is not possible to defend his weakness on f7. All white pieces are ready for the battle, while black has only managed to develop a bishop and a knight. }
10... Qxd4
{ Black grabs another pawn, but his king will find himself in trouble. } 11.
Bxe6 Qxe5 12. Bxf7+ Kd8 13. Bh4
{ The position is totally winning for White. We are bringing the rooks to the attack with O-O-O, Rhe1, Bg3. With an exposed king and uncoordinated pieces, Black will not survive for long. }
