[Black "Levon Aronian vs. Maxime Vachier Lagrave, Gibraltar Masters, 2018"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 g6 3. Nc3 d5 4. Bf4 Bg7 5. Nb5 Na6 6. e3 c6 7. Nc3 O-O
{ It is not good for Black to allow his pawn structure compromised.  7...Nb8  is better, which transposes toa position analyzed in Part I. }
8. Bxa6 bxa6 9. h3
{ 9.Ne5  This improvement ismentioned in Part I. White's knights totally dominate the center, controlling the key squares of c5 and e5.  9...Qb6  10.b3  This move not only defends the pawn but also prepares for Na4. Black does not have any counterplay.  10...Nh5  11.O-O  Nxf4  12.exf4⩲  White has a risk-free position thanks to his active pieces and better pawn structure. }
9... Nd7 10. O-O Bb7 11. Na4 Rc8
{ After this move, Black's position became very difficult. His bishop on b7 is useless, and he has many weaknesses on the queenside.   Black's only chance to stay in the game is to open up more space for his light-squared bishop with  11...c5!  12.c3   12.Nxc5  Black gets back the pawn right away with his next two moves.  12...Nxc5  13.dxc5  Rc8∞  12...c4  13.b4⩲  White still has a small advantage even here, as White's pawn structure is superior. The plan for White is Nc5 and create a passed pawn on the queenside. }
12. b4
{ This move is necessary to stop ...c5.  Now the position is closed, and the black bishops are passive. }
12... a5 13. Nc5 Nxc5 14. bxc5
{ White has complete control over the b-file thanks to the powerful London bishop. Black's queenside pawns on a7, a5, c6 are very weak. }
14... Ba6 15. Re1 a4 16. Qd2 Bb5 17. e4
{ This is a good plan. White opens the e-file for his rooks and creates kingside threats such as Bh6. }
17... dxe4 18. Rxe4 Bc4 19. Bh6
{ White should not  have rushed with this bishop exchange. Instead, he needed to consolidate and centralize all his pieces.   The simple  19.Rae1  is stronger than the game move. White doubles the rooks to attack the black pawn on e7. }
19... Bxh6
{ After this move Black is lost as his kingside is not defensible.  19...Bd5  instead gives Black decent drawing chances after  20.Bxg7  Kxg7  21.Re3  . White is still slightly better, but Black has made a lot of progress  activating his light-squared bishop from b7 to d5. }
20. Qxh6 f6 21. Nd2 Bd5 22. Re3 Rb8 23. c4 Bf7 24. Re4 g5 25. Rae1 e5 26. dxe5
