11... c5
{ 11...Ne6!  would have been very strong. Black gains a tempo and counterattacks in the center.  12.Be3  c5∓  White has serious problems with his central pawns. }
12. e5 Ne4 13. Re1 Ne6 14. Bh2 cxd4
{ The position is equal after this move. Instead,  14...Rc8  would maintain the pressure in the center. }
