7... dxe3
{ This capture, in my opinion, leads to a difficult position for Black.   7...dxc3  8.Qa4+=∞  Seemy analysis in Part II. }
8. Ba3 exd2+ 9. Qxd2
{ As Black cannot castle short, his king does not feel safe. White has more than enough compensation thanks to the bishop pair and potential for a queenside attack. }
9... Nc6 10. Qg5 Rg8
{ This is a sad move to make, but Black does not have a choice. } 11. Bd3 h6
12. Qe3 Qb6 13. Qe2
{ Of course, White should keep the queens on the board to continue the attack on the black king. White's plan is very simple: to castle short and open up the queenside and center. }
13... Bd7 14. O-O O-O-O 15. b4 Kb8
{ After this move, Black is lost without any counterplay.   15...e5  This is Black's only chance to muddy the waters.  16.b5  e4  17.bxc6  Bxc6∞ }
16. b5 Na5 17. Ne5 Be8 18. Bb4
{ Even though Black is up a pawn, he has no good move as all his pieces are misplaced and passive. }
