{ 5.h3  This move is my recommendation, but it often transposes anyway. } 5...
Bg7 6. h3 O-O 7. e3 c5 8. Nbd2 Qb6 9. Be2 Nc6 10. O-O Bf5
{ Black played normal moves, but she was already slightly worse. The pawn on c5 does not work well with the bishop on g7.   10...cxd4  11.exd4  The c3-d4 pawn chain is very useful in limiting Black's dark-squared bishop. White has a clear plan to play in the center and queenside. }
11. Qb3 c4 12. Qa3 Rfe8 13. b3 cxb3 14. axb3 Ne4 15. Nxe4 Bxe4 16. Rfd1 a6 17.
